Good question! Unit tests are simple, standalone functions in your module with a `#[cfg(test)]` attribute. They can test private items too. Integration tests live inside the `tests/` directory. You import everything from your lib and test how modules work together. For example:

```rust
// src/lib.rs
pub fn add_two(a: i32) -> i32 {
    a + 2
}
```
Then in tests/integration_test.rs:

```rust
#[cfg(test)]
mod integration_test {
    use super::*;
    #[test]
    fn test_add_two() {
        assert_eq!(add_two(3), 5);
    }
}
```
